<p>In a recent <em>Freeman</em> article, &#8220;Check Your Context,&#8221; columnist Sarah Skwire brought my attention to a popular meme on the political left, both online and off: &#8220;Check your privilege.&#8221;</p>
<p>At its gentlest, this is advice to raise our awareness of those aspects of our personal histories that may lead to complacent assumptions about how the world works, assumptions that may limit the scope of our moral imaginations.</p>
<p>When it is less gentle (which is often), it is a dismissal of the opinions of anyone who is insufficiently poor, or, more likely, insufficiently left-wing. <a href="http://www.fee.org/the_freeman/detail/check-your-history">[Read the rest of the article.]</a></p>
